<topic id='business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Accident and Emergency Episode - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode">Accident and Emergency Episode</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode">Accident and Emergency Episode</xref>
 involves visits to an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 of one 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 for a particular incident. The 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 may receive treatment during the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode">Accident and Emergency Episode</xref>
 from the accident and emergency service and from other 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_main_specialty">MAIN SPECIALTIES</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
Each 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode">Accident and Emergency Episode</xref>
 takes place at a single 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 and consists of one or more 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_episode">Accident and Emergency Episode</xref>
 may give rise to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
